WEBVTT

00:03.046 --> 00:06.397
THIS IS MY DATE OUTFIT.IS THIS YOUR FIRST DATE? I MEAN,
UM, SINCE YOUR WIFE DIED.

00:06.397 --> 00:09.009
DO I SEEM OUT OF PRACTICE? RED JOHN,
IF YOU'RE LISTENING TO US NOW,

00:09.009 --> 00:12.273
I URGE YOU TO REACH OUT
AND GET HELP.

00:12.273 --> 00:14.492
YOU CAN CHANGE.[Patrick] WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU THINKING?

00:14.492 --> 00:16.842
DON'T YOU UNDERSTAND
WHO YOU'RE DEALING WITH?

00:16.842 --> 00:19.845
RED JOHN IS NOT
COMING AFTER ME.ARE YOU BLIND?
YOU'VE DONE EXACTLY WHAT I DID,

00:19.845 --> 00:21.804
AND HE KILLED
MY WIFE AND CHILD.

00:21.804 --> 00:23.501
[Van Pelt] KRISTINA?

00:23.501 --> 00:25.590
[Patrick] RED JOHN COULD'VE
GOTTEN IN AND TAKEN HER,

00:25.590 --> 00:27.984
OR MAYBE
HE LURED HER OUT SOMEHOW.

00:27.984 --> 00:29.377
[man] AAH!

00:29.377 --> 00:32.380
"TIGER, TIGER,
BURNING BRIGHT..."

00:32.380 --> 00:34.860
"IN THE FORESTS
OF THE NIGHT,

00:34.860 --> 00:37.341
"WHAT IMMORTAL HAND OR EYE

00:37.341 --> 00:39.169
COULD FRAME
THY FEARFUL SYMMETRY?"

00:39.169 --> 00:41.215
[gunshot][gasps]

00:41.215 --> 00:45.045
I ALMOST FORGOT. KRISTINA WOULD
WANT ME TO SEND HER LOVE.

00:47.656 --> 00:50.528
[indistinct conversations]

00:57.361 --> 01:00.060
[police radio chatter]

01:00.060 --> 01:01.757
YOU CAN'T PARK THERE.

01:01.757 --> 01:03.628
SURE, I CAN. LOOK.

01:06.109 --> 01:07.719
[man] Roger. Stand by.

01:07.719 --> 01:10.331
[speaks indistinctly]
We'll call you back.

01:10.331 --> 01:11.767
THERE YOU ARE.

01:11.767 --> 01:13.203
HERE I AM. GOOD MORNING.

01:13.203 --> 01:15.336
WHY SO GLUM?

01:15.336 --> 01:17.729
THIS IS HARVEY DUBLIN.

01:17.729 --> 01:21.298
THAT'S HIS CHAUFFEUR PETER RUSSO
WITH THREE BULLETS IN HIM.

01:21.298 --> 01:23.431
THAT'S HIS CAR.
MR. DUBLIN'S GONE.

01:23.431 --> 01:25.128
ABDUCTED, IT LOOKS LIKE.

01:28.827 --> 01:29.915
HARVEY DUBLIN?

01:29.915 --> 01:31.743
BIG-TIME STATEHOUSE LOBBYIST,

01:31.743 --> 01:35.704
LAWYER, KINGMAKER.
FAMOUS AND WELL-CONNECTED.

01:35.704 --> 01:37.532
AH, THE EVIL TWINS.

01:37.532 --> 01:40.448
BRASS AND MEDIA ARE GONNA BE
ALL OVER US LIKE SUCKERFISH.

01:40.448 --> 01:43.015
OH, WHY DON'T WE JUST GIVE IT TO
THE FBI? THEY LOVE THAT STUFF.

01:43.015 --> 01:45.409
OH, I WISH. TOO LATE.

01:45.409 --> 01:47.368
THE NEW BOSS IS HERE DOING
ON-CAMERAS. IT'S OUR BABY.

01:47.368 --> 01:49.326
NEW BOSS?
I THOUGHT HIGHTOWER WAS BOSS.

01:49.326 --> 01:51.372
THE BOSS OF HIGHTOWER.

01:51.372 --> 01:53.374
THE DIRECTOR
OF THE ENTIRE DIVISION.

01:53.374 --> 01:56.116
I TOLD YOU ABOUT HIM LAST WEEK.
YOUR MEMORY'S GOING.

01:56.116 --> 01:58.944
MY MEMORY IS A MIGHTY FORTRESS,
LISBON,

01:58.944 --> 02:02.948
FROM WHICH NO FACT
EVER ESCAPES ONCE COMMITTED.

02:02.948 --> 02:05.037
NOW WHEN YOU TELL ME
BORING THINGS,

02:05.037 --> 02:07.344
I SET 'EM FREE IMMEDIATELY.

02:07.344 --> 02:08.824
SAVES OVERCROWDING.

02:10.217 --> 02:12.610
HARVEY DUBLIN IS MISSING.

02:12.610 --> 02:14.656
IT LOOKS LIKE A KIDNAPPING,

02:14.656 --> 02:18.312
PRESUMABLY FOR RANSOM,
BUT WE CAN'T BE SURE AT PRESENT.

02:18.312 --> 02:21.793
WE SHALL HAVE TO AWAIT
FURTHER DEVELOPMENTS.

02:21.793 --> 02:25.319
HARVEY IS A PILLAR OF THIS CITY,
ONE OF THE GOOD GUYS.

02:25.319 --> 02:28.583
WE ARE ALL PRAYING
FOR HIS SAFETY.

02:28.583 --> 02:31.063
THANK YOU.[woman] OVER HERE, MR. BERTRAM.
ONE MORE QUESTION FOR ME?

02:31.063 --> 02:32.717
IDIOT.

02:32.717 --> 02:34.806
YOU AND YOUR SNAP JUDGMENTS.
WHAT IS HE SUPPOSED TO SAY?

02:34.806 --> 02:38.462
WHY DOES HE HAVE TO
SAY ANYTHING?

02:38.462 --> 02:41.248
WHAT'S YOUR TAKE ON THIS?

02:41.248 --> 02:42.640
HMM.

02:42.640 --> 02:44.207
I DON'T KNOW.

02:46.601 --> 02:48.820
[woman] MR. BERTRAM, OVER HERE.
CAN I HAVE YOUR ATTENTION?

02:48.820 --> 02:51.345
EH, I THINK I'LL GIVE THIS ONE
A MISS.

02:51.345 --> 02:53.303
A MISS?
WHAT DO YOU MEAN "A MISS"?

02:53.303 --> 02:56.176
I JUST FEEL THIS ONE
IS NOT FOR ME.

02:56.176 --> 02:58.569
I'LL CATCH THE NEXT ONE,
I-I-I PROMISE.

02:58.569 --> 03:01.181
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
YOU'RE NOT GONNA--

03:01.181 --> 03:03.444
AGENT LISBON, I BELIEVE?
AND MR. JANE?YES. HI.

03:03.444 --> 03:05.489
DIRECTOR BERTRAM
WILL SPEAK TO YOU NOW.

03:05.489 --> 03:08.318
WE'RE ON A SUPERTIGHT SCHEDULE.
HE APPRECIATE FACTS AND BREVITY.

03:08.318 --> 03:09.276
OKAY?

03:09.276 --> 03:10.407
AGENT LISBON.

03:10.407 --> 03:12.757
YES, SIR, DIRECTOR BERTRAM.

03:12.757 --> 03:15.717
[chuckles] AND YOU MUST BE
OUR BOY WONDER PATRICK JANE.

03:15.717 --> 03:18.589
I'VE HEARD A LOT
OF GOOD THINGS ABOUT YOU.HI. NICE TO MEET YOU, SIR.

03:18.589 --> 03:21.375
NOW I WANT THIS RESOLVED
A.S.A.P.

03:21.375 --> 03:23.899
WHATEVER IT TAKES. THE HECK
WITH OVERTIME RESTRICTIONS.

03:23.899 --> 03:26.423
YOU DO THE HOURS,
I'LL FIND THE FUNDING.

03:26.423 --> 03:29.644
WE ARE ALL IN THIS TOGETHER
AS ONE.

03:29.644 --> 03:32.342
THAT'S WHAT I'M ALL ABOUT.OH, WE ARE ON IT, SIR.

03:32.342 --> 03:34.301
UH, YEAH, I WON'T BE WORKING
THIS PARTICULAR CASE,

03:34.301 --> 03:36.041
BUT I-I DO LIKE
WHAT YOU SAID.

03:36.041 --> 03:37.478
WE'RE ALL IN THIS TOGETHER
AS ONE. MAO TSE-TUNG, RIGHT?

03:37.478 --> 03:40.263
NOW HOLD YOUR HORSES THERE,
BUSTER.

03:40.263 --> 03:43.179
WHAT DO YOU MEAN YOU WON'T
WORKING ON THIS ONE?WELL, STATEHOUSE LOBBYIST
ABDUCTIONS--

03:43.179 --> 03:45.225
IT'S, UH, NOT REALLY
MY CUP OF TEA.

03:45.225 --> 03:48.880
WELL, THAT'S--THAT'S KIND OF
UNPROFESSIONAL, DON'T YOU THINK?

03:48.880 --> 03:51.187
I GUESS, BUT I'M NOT ACTUALLY
A PROFESSIONAL.

03:51.187 --> 03:53.058
QUESTION FOR YOU.

03:53.058 --> 03:55.322
W-WHY ARE YOU HERE?
ASIDE FROM THE CAMERAS.

03:55.322 --> 03:58.542
OH, WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
"ASIDEFROM THE CAMERAS"?

03:58.542 --> 04:01.110
PUBLIC PERCEPTION
IS AN IMPORTANT TOOL.

04:01.110 --> 04:02.372
MM.

04:02.372 --> 04:03.678
TOOL.OOH.

04:05.941 --> 04:07.943
YOU JUST PUT YOUR HAND
ON ME.

04:07.943 --> 04:09.727
NO. I MEAN, YES, BUT--

04:09.727 --> 04:12.295
YES, YOU DID.
DON'T EVER DO THAT AGAIN.

04:12.295 --> 04:14.210
[chuckles] OR ELSE WHAT?

04:16.517 --> 04:19.520
YOU EVER SMELL A DEAD MOUSE?
DO YOU REMEMBER THAT SMELL?

04:19.520 --> 04:21.478
YES.

04:21.478 --> 04:23.219
WELL, I JUST NOW

04:23.219 --> 04:25.221
PUT A DEAD MOUSE
IN YOUR JACKET POCKET.

04:25.221 --> 04:28.137
AND NO MATTER HOW MANY TIMES
YOU CLEAN THAT JACKET,

04:28.137 --> 04:31.358
YOU'LL ALWAYS SMELL THAT
DEAD MOUSE, AND YOU'LL REMEMBER

04:31.358 --> 04:34.317
THAT YOU SHOULD NEVER
HAVE PUT YOUR HAND ON ME.

04:37.755 --> 04:40.323
AAH! YOU SON OF A BITCH.

04:40.323 --> 04:43.413
IT'S ACTUALLY JUST
A WADDED UP NAPKIN

04:43.413 --> 04:45.546
BUT, UH, HAS
THE SAME PSYCHOLOGICAL EFFECT.

04:45.546 --> 04:47.548
HUMAN MIND IS FUNNY THAT WAY.

04:47.548 --> 04:49.593
GOOD TO MEET YOU, SIR.
SORRY, LISBON.

04:52.553 --> 04:55.860
HE HAD A ROUGH SUMMER.

04:55.860 --> 04:59.255
♪♪

05:06.001 --> 05:08.003
[Lisbon] RIGSBY AND VAN PELT
ARE CANVASSING

05:08.003 --> 05:10.005
THE AREA
AROUND THE ABDUCTION SITE.

05:10.005 --> 05:12.224
CHO'S WITH MRS. DUBLIN,
WAITING FOR A RANSOM DEMAND,

05:12.224 --> 05:14.618
AND TECH SERVICES
ARE UP AND RUNNING.

05:14.618 --> 05:17.665
WELL, THIS IS A SCARY ONE.
LOTS OF ATTENTION.

05:17.665 --> 05:19.710
KEEP MOLLY IN PUBLIC AFFAIRS

05:19.710 --> 05:21.930
APPRISED OF ANY GOOD STUFF
WE CAN FEED THE MEDIA,

05:21.930 --> 05:23.323
KEEP THEM ON OUR SIDE,

05:23.323 --> 05:25.629
AND DON'T MAKE ANY MISTAKES.

05:25.629 --> 05:27.501
NO, MA'AM.

05:27.501 --> 05:29.894
HOW'S JANE?[sets down cup]

05:29.894 --> 05:31.940
THE SAME.

05:31.940 --> 05:34.290
YOU THINK HE'S IN DANGER
OF CRACKING UP?

05:34.290 --> 05:35.335
NO.

05:37.380 --> 05:41.166
I MEAN, NO. WELL, I DON'T
THINK SO. I THINK HE'LL BE FINE.

05:41.166 --> 05:43.168
[papers rustle]

05:43.168 --> 05:45.562
THAT'S NOT VERY CONVINCING,
LISBON.

05:45.562 --> 05:49.174
WHAT HE'S BEEN THROUGH
WOULD BREAK ANYONE.

05:49.174 --> 05:51.220
HE'S NOT GONNA CRACK UP.

05:51.220 --> 05:54.092
I THINK SOME TIME OFF
WILL DO HIM GOOD, THOUGH.

05:54.092 --> 05:57.400
YEAH, WELL, NO CAN DO.

05:57.400 --> 05:59.576
BERTRAM WANTS HIM
ON THE DUBLIN CASE.

05:59.576 --> 06:02.536
AFTER JANE WAS SO RUDE TO HIM?BERTRAM'S ALL BOTTOM LINE.

06:02.536 --> 06:04.625
HE WON'T LET PERSONAL ISSUES
INTRUDE.

06:04.625 --> 06:07.628
JANE'S THE BEST ASSET WE HAVE,
AND BERTRAM KNOWS THAT.

06:07.628 --> 06:11.980
BUT JANE DOESN'T WANT
TO BE ON THE CASE.CHANGE HIS MIND.

06:11.980 --> 06:16.376
I'M NOT GONNA TELL BERTRAM
WE CAN'T CONTROL OUR OWN PEOPLE.

06:20.205 --> 06:23.208
I HAVE AN IDEA
AS TO HOW TO PERSUADE HIM,

06:23.208 --> 06:25.689
BUT IT'S KIND OF UNETHICAL.

06:25.689 --> 06:27.343
I DON'T WANNA KNOW.

06:34.306 --> 06:35.438
WHERE'S JANE?

06:35.438 --> 06:36.657
UPSTAIRS.

06:36.657 --> 06:37.745
THANKS.

06:48.843 --> 06:51.411
[knocks on door]JANE?

06:51.411 --> 06:53.413
COME IN.

06:53.413 --> 06:54.936
HEY.

06:54.936 --> 06:56.372
NICE PLACE.

06:56.372 --> 07:00.507
[sighs] YEAH. YEAH, I
LIKE THE VIEW AND THE QUIET.

07:04.902 --> 07:07.427
AND WHAT ARE YOU DOING
WITH ALL THE QUIET?

07:07.427 --> 07:11.343
JUST THINKING.

07:11.343 --> 07:13.345
JANE, YOU HAVE TO STOP
BLAMING YOURSELF.

07:13.345 --> 07:16.218
IF RED JOHN TOOK KRISTINA FRYE,
IT'S NOT YOUR--

07:16.218 --> 07:17.741
THERE'S NO "IF."
HE TOOK HER.

07:17.741 --> 07:20.701
IFHE DID,
YOU CAN'T BLAME YOURSELF.

07:20.701 --> 07:22.746
BESIDES, WHAT GOOD IS IT
TO SIT UP HERE,

07:22.746 --> 07:25.575
SCRIBBLING IN YOUR BOOK? YOU'RE
NOT GONNA FIND HER THAT WAY.

07:25.575 --> 07:27.359
[chuckles]

07:27.359 --> 07:29.361
I'M NOT GONNA
CHANGE MY MIND.

07:29.361 --> 07:31.973
I DON'T WANT TO WORK
THE DUBLIN CASE.

07:31.973 --> 07:35.324
THAT'S FINE. IT'S A DONE DEAL.
I UNDERSTAND.

07:35.324 --> 07:38.588
IT'D BE GOOD FOR YOU
TO HAVE A BREAK.

07:38.588 --> 07:41.809
LISTEN,
ON A COMPLETELY OTHER SUBJECT,

07:41.809 --> 07:44.899
I NEED A PERSONAL FAVOR.

07:44.899 --> 07:46.901
I'D LIKE YOU
TO COME AND MEET SOMEONE.

07:46.901 --> 07:48.990
WHO?I CAN'T TELL.

07:48.990 --> 07:51.079
WHY NOT?

07:51.079 --> 07:53.690
I PROMISE IT HAS NOTHING
TO DO WITH HARVEY DUBLIN.

07:53.690 --> 07:55.692
YOU'RE TRYING
TO PLAY ME SOMEHOW,

07:55.692 --> 07:58.173
CONVINCE ME
TO CHANGE MY MIND.

07:58.173 --> 08:00.001
NO.YES, YOU ARE.

08:01.393 --> 08:03.613
AND I GUESS I OWE YOU A SHOT.

08:03.613 --> 08:06.181
BUT IT'S NOT GONNA WORK,
WHATEVER IT IS.

08:14.972 --> 08:19.324
HEY, CHO, HOW'S IT GOIN'
WITH MRS. DUBLIN?

08:19.324 --> 08:22.284
NOTHING SO FAR. WHEN'S SOMEBODY
COMING TO RELIEVE ME HERE?

08:22.284 --> 08:24.329
WHY? WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

08:24.329 --> 08:26.941
NOTHING. I'LL CALL IF WE GET
ANY DEVELOPMENTS.

08:26.941 --> 08:28.943
WHAT IS IT? IS IT HARVEY?

08:28.943 --> 08:30.379
NO, MA'AM.

08:30.379 --> 08:32.642
[cries] OH, MY GOD!

08:32.642 --> 08:35.427
I AM GONNA EXPLODE!
I CAN'T STAND IT!

08:35.427 --> 08:38.169
I CAN'T TAKE IT!
I SWEAR TO GOD!

08:38.169 --> 08:39.954
[sobs]

08:39.954 --> 08:42.043
WHY, KIMBALL? [sniffles]

08:42.043 --> 08:46.177
WHY AM I BEING PUNISHED?
I'M A GOOD PERSON.

08:46.177 --> 08:47.788
YES, MA'AM.

08:47.788 --> 08:49.703
STOP CALLING ME "MA'AM."

08:49.703 --> 08:52.357
I'M NOT YOUR GRANDMOTHER.
[sniffles]

08:52.357 --> 08:55.404
HOW OLD DO YOU THINK I AM
ANYWAY?

08:55.404 --> 08:58.015
48, 49.

08:58.015 --> 09:00.975
[sobbing]

09:06.415 --> 09:08.765
I GET THE PICTURE.DO YOU?

09:08.765 --> 09:13.248
YEAH, DUBLIN'S DRIVER--
THE DEAD GUY, PETE RUSSO, RIGHT?

09:13.248 --> 09:14.728
HE HAS FAMILY.

09:14.728 --> 09:16.730
HE WASN'T WEARING
A WEDDING RING, SO, UH...

09:16.730 --> 09:19.123
[doorbell rings]WE'RE ABOUT TO MEET A, UH...

09:19.123 --> 09:21.430
[door squeaks]

09:21.430 --> 09:25.086
YES. EXACTLY.

09:25.086 --> 09:26.566
YES, WHO ARE YOU?

09:26.566 --> 09:29.307
NADINE, I'M AGENT LISBON
WITH THE CBI.

09:29.307 --> 09:32.180
WE SPOKE ON THE PHONE.
THIS IS PATRICK JANE.

09:32.180 --> 09:34.704
HI. YOU'RE, UH,
PETE RUSSO'S DAUGHTER?

09:34.704 --> 09:36.140
UH, YEAH.

09:38.490 --> 09:39.883
HELLO?THEY'RE POLICE.

09:39.883 --> 09:41.885
[whispers] OH, OKAY.THIS IS MY MOM.

09:41.885 --> 09:44.627
[normal voice] PATRICIA.

09:44.627 --> 09:46.498
AND THIS IS KEITH,
MY STEPDAD.

09:46.498 --> 09:49.327
HI. UM...

09:49.327 --> 09:51.286
PLEASE COME IN.

09:54.724 --> 09:56.247
[sighs]

09:59.599 --> 10:02.471
MISS LISBON SAYS YOU'RE THE BEST
DETECTIVE IN CALIFORNIA.

10:06.693 --> 10:11.088
SHE SAYS IF ANYBODY CAN FIND
WHO KILLED MY FATHER, YOU CAN.

10:11.088 --> 10:13.134
I JUST HAVE TO SAY,

10:13.134 --> 10:16.398
I DIDN'T THINK YOU WOULD STOOP
TO SUCH CRUDE MANIPULATION.

10:16.398 --> 10:18.052
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

10:18.052 --> 10:20.445
INSIDE JOKE. I'M SORRY.

10:20.445 --> 10:23.884
UH, I WILL FIND WHO KILLED YOUR
FATHER AND ABDUCTED MR. DUBLIN.

10:23.884 --> 10:25.712
AN INSIDE JOKE?

10:25.712 --> 10:28.149
HER FATHER IS DEAD.

10:28.149 --> 10:29.803
MURDERED.

10:29.803 --> 10:31.282
YOU'RE MAKING JOKES?

10:33.110 --> 10:35.112
YES, UH, IT'S A FAULT OF MINE.

10:35.112 --> 10:37.114
UH, WHAT IT IS, THE JOKE?

10:37.114 --> 10:40.552
UH, I HAVE A--I HAVE A LOT
ON MIND RIGHT NOW.

10:40.552 --> 10:43.077
UH, I DIDN'T REALLY WANNA COME
TO WORK TODAY,

10:43.077 --> 10:45.296
BUT MY GOOD FRIEND AND COLLEAGUE
AGENT LISBON

10:45.296 --> 10:47.472
TRICKED ME INTO MEETING YOU,

10:47.472 --> 10:49.344
KNOWING THAT
I COULDN'T REFUSE YOU

10:49.344 --> 10:51.607
BECAUSE YOU'RE THE AGE
MY DAUGHTER WOULD BE

10:51.607 --> 10:55.350
IF SHE WERE STILL ALIVE,
IF SHE HADN'T BEEN MURDERED.[gasps] OH, GOODNESS.

10:55.350 --> 10:57.613
MURDERED BY A MAN NAMED
RED JOHN,

10:57.613 --> 10:59.659
WHOM I MET WITH RECENTLY.

10:59.659 --> 11:02.270
HE SAVED MY LIFE
AND ABDUCTED A FRIEND OF MINE.

11:02.270 --> 11:05.186
LONG STORY.
HENCE, MANY THINGS ON MY MIND.

11:05.186 --> 11:06.361
[slurps]

11:06.361 --> 11:09.146
THAT'S NOT
A VERY FUNNY JOKE.

11:09.146 --> 11:10.713
HMM.

11:10.713 --> 11:12.759
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOUR FRIEND?

11:12.759 --> 11:14.630
STILL MISSING.

11:14.630 --> 11:18.373
UH, PLEASE,
TELL US ABOUT YOUR FATHER.

11:18.373 --> 11:21.158
HE WAS A GOOD PERSON.

11:21.158 --> 11:24.727
HE WAS... FUNNY

11:24.727 --> 11:27.208
AND... [voice breaks]
AND GENEROUS.

11:27.208 --> 11:30.733
AND I COULD TALK TO HIM ABOUT
ANYTHING, AND HE WOULD LISTEN.

11:30.733 --> 11:32.692
[Patricia] OH, YES,
HE COULD BE CHARMING.

11:35.216 --> 11:36.826
HE HAD HIS WAYS.

11:36.826 --> 11:40.395
WHAT KIND OF WAYS?HE HAD A TEMPER.

11:40.395 --> 11:44.312
THAT HE DID.

11:44.312 --> 11:46.706
I MEAN, HIS HEART WAS
IN THE RIGHT PLACE, YOU KNOW?

11:48.620 --> 11:51.188
WHATEVER HIS FAULTS,

11:51.188 --> 11:53.364
HE DIDN'T DESERVE TO DIE
THIS WAY.

11:54.801 --> 11:57.325
REALLY, I'M IMPRESSED.

11:57.325 --> 12:00.937
YOU--YOU PLAYED ME LIKE A FISH
AND--AND YOU LIED TO ME.I KIND OF DID, DIDN'T I? SORRY.

12:00.937 --> 12:04.375
NO, I'M GLAD TO SEE YOU'RE
FINALLY LEARNING A FEW THINGS.

12:04.375 --> 12:07.335
OF COURSE, UH,
NOW I SHALL HAVE MY REVENGE.WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

12:07.335 --> 12:10.251
[chuckles] AHH.

12:10.251 --> 12:12.644
[Rigsby] DON'T WORRY.
WE'RE NOT HERE ABOUT DRUGS.

12:12.644 --> 12:15.125
WE'RE HERE ABOUT THE KILLING
THE OTHER NIGHT.

12:15.125 --> 12:17.084
[man] AH, YEAH, YEAH.
I HEARD ABOUT THAT.

12:17.084 --> 12:19.608
KIDNAPPED A MAN, HUH?
THAT'S TOO BAD.

12:19.608 --> 12:21.958
LOCAL BEAT COPS SAY YOU GUYS
DO BUSINESS UNDER THAT BRIDGE.YEAH, LOOK,

12:21.958 --> 12:25.353
THE LOCAL BEAT COPS ARE NICE
GUYS, BUT THEY'RE OUT OF TOUCH.

12:25.353 --> 12:28.095
WE DON'T DO BUSINESS UNDER THAT
BRIDGE. THE HOS--THEY GOT DIBS.

12:28.095 --> 12:31.489
YOU'RE GONNA WANNA TALK
TO THE LADIES OVER ON FREMONT.

12:31.489 --> 12:33.970
ALL RIGHT. THANKS.YEAH, NO WORRIES.

12:33.970 --> 12:36.407
HEY, HEY, RED.

12:36.407 --> 12:38.627
YOU--YOU EVER DATE
A HUSTLER BEFORE?

12:38.627 --> 12:40.977
NOT SO FAR!

12:40.977 --> 12:43.240
WHAT? I'M KIDDING.

12:47.331 --> 12:48.768
THANK YOU.

12:48.768 --> 12:51.553
YEAH. OKAY.
GOOD TO KNOW.

12:51.553 --> 12:54.730
GOOD AFTERNOON. REID COLMAN. I'M
MR. DUBLIN'S PERSONAL LAWYER.

12:54.730 --> 12:57.472
GLAD TO SEE YOU PEOPLE.
YOU MADE ANY PROGRESS?

12:57.472 --> 13:01.258
EARLY DAYS, MR. COLMAN.YOU'LL, UH, NEED
TO TALK TO ME, YES?

13:01.258 --> 13:04.392
NOW'S A GOOD TIME.
I HAVE TEN MINUTES OR SO.

13:04.392 --> 13:07.525
IF YOU'LL COME THIS WAY,
WE CAN USE THE CONFERENCE ROOM.

13:07.525 --> 13:09.571
UH, JUST A MOMENT.

13:09.571 --> 13:10.964
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

13:10.964 --> 13:12.966
MARJORIE.

13:12.966 --> 13:15.011
MARJORIE.
THAT'S A VERY NICE NAME.

13:15.011 --> 13:17.013
I'D LIKE TO SPEAK
TO MARJORIE FIRST, THANKS.[sighs]

13:17.013 --> 13:19.973
UH, WE WILL NEED TO SPEAK
TO YOU IN DUE COURSE, SIR.

13:19.973 --> 13:21.931
I'LL, UH, TRY
AND FIT YOU IN LATER.

13:21.931 --> 13:23.977
PROSTITUTES? NO. NO.

13:23.977 --> 13:26.806
MR. DUBLIN WAS NOT
THAT SORT OF MAN AT ALL.

13:26.806 --> 13:28.720
THE ALLEYWAY
FROM WHICH HE WAS ABDUCTED

13:28.720 --> 13:30.418
WAS USED BY PROSTITUTES,

13:30.418 --> 13:33.334
AND IT WAS NOWHERE NEAR
MR. DUBLIN'S REGULAR ROUTE.

13:33.334 --> 13:35.162
I HAVE BEEN
MR. DUBLIN'S PERSONAL SECRETARY

13:35.162 --> 13:36.728
FOR TEN YEARS,

13:36.728 --> 13:39.470
AND I CAN TELL YOU
WITHOUT A SHADOW OF A DOUBT

13:39.470 --> 13:41.168
THAT HE IS

13:41.168 --> 13:43.910
THE MOST DECENT, CARING,
CLEAN, GENEROUS HUMAN BEING

13:43.910 --> 13:45.912
THAT ANYONE COULD HOPE
TO MEET.

13:45.912 --> 13:48.305
WE WANT TO BRING HIM BACK
SAFELY, MARJORIE.

13:48.305 --> 13:50.177
WE NEED
TO KNOW EVERYTHING.

13:57.837 --> 14:00.883
USUALLY I CAN GET AHOLD
OF HIM AT ANY TIME.

14:00.883 --> 14:03.494
HIS WORK DEMANDS IT,
BUT ONCE IN A WHILE,

14:03.494 --> 14:06.019
HE'D DISAPPEAR
FOR AN HOUR OR SO,

14:06.019 --> 14:08.804
NO--NO ANSWER FROM HIM
OR HIS DRIVER.

14:08.804 --> 14:11.502
HOW OFTEN WAS THAT?EVERY COUPLE OF WEEKS.

14:11.502 --> 14:14.462
A REGULAR DATE RIGHT AROUND
THE TIME HE WAS ABDUCTED, YES?

14:16.551 --> 14:19.554
AND WHAT DID YOU THINK
HE MIGHT BE DOING?

14:19.554 --> 14:22.296
MISTRESS, I THOUGHT,

14:22.296 --> 14:23.863
BUT NOT THIS.

14:23.863 --> 14:27.823
MEN HAVE NEEDS.
I UNDERSTAND THAT.

14:27.823 --> 14:30.913
PLEASE, YOU'LL FIND HIM,
WON'T YOU? YOU'LL FIND HIM?

14:30.913 --> 14:33.437
MARJORIE, UH,
I HAVE TO TELL YOU,

14:33.437 --> 14:36.092
UH, IT'S VERY LIKELY
THAT HE'S ALREADY DEAD.

14:36.092 --> 14:39.617
WHOA. WAIT A MINUTE.
WE DON'T KNOW THAT.

14:39.617 --> 14:43.012
IT'S A HUNCH THAT I HAVE,
AND IF I'M RIGHT,

14:43.012 --> 14:45.928
IT'S A BLESSING FOR YOU.

14:45.928 --> 14:48.670
UNREQUITED LOVE IS
A TERRIBLE THING.

14:48.670 --> 14:51.542
YOU HAVE TO FIND YOURSELF A MAN
THAT WILL LOVE YOU BACK.

14:51.542 --> 14:54.415
YOU'RE A GOOD WOMAN. YOU
DESERVE IT. THINK ABOUT THAT.

15:03.467 --> 15:06.427
SO THIS WAS DONE BY SOMEONE WHO
KNEW ABOUT DUBLIN'S ROUTINE--

15:06.427 --> 15:07.863
SOMEONE VERY CLOSE.

15:07.863 --> 15:10.126
WH-WHY DID YOU SAY
HE WAS DEAD?

15:10.126 --> 15:12.520
BECAUSE HE IS. HE'S DEAD,
AND IT'S NOT A KIDNAPPING.GIVE ME A REASON.

15:12.520 --> 15:15.131
I'LL BET YOU
ALL THE TEA IN CHINA.[cell phone rings]

15:15.131 --> 15:17.481
[scoffs]
THAT IS NOT A REASON.I'LL GIVE YOU GOOD ODDS.

15:17.481 --> 15:19.483
[ring]HEY.

15:19.483 --> 15:21.877
HEY. RANSOM DEMAND
CAME THROUGH.

15:21.877 --> 15:23.531
HOW MUCH?

15:23.531 --> 15:25.446
ALL RIGHT.
WE'RE ON OUR WAY.

15:25.446 --> 15:28.231
A MILLION DOLLARS FOR
THE SAFE RETURN OF DUBLIN--

15:28.231 --> 15:30.625
THAT KINDA SOUNDS LIKE
A KIDNAPPING, DOESN'T IT?

15:30.625 --> 15:33.715
DOESN'T MEAN IT'S A KIDNAPPING.
DOESN'T MEAN HE'S NOT DEAD.

15:33.715 --> 15:37.197
IS THIS A SERIOUS THEORY,
OR IS THIS YOUR REVENGE?

15:48.295 --> 15:50.819
[Cho] THIS WAS SENT
FROM A THROWAWAY PHONE.

15:50.819 --> 15:53.909
"DO EXACTLY AS INSTRUCTED
OR H.D. GETS HIS THROAT CUT

15:53.909 --> 15:56.868
"AND WE SEND YOU HIS TONGUE.
WE WANT A MILLION DOLLARS

15:56.868 --> 15:59.393
"IN USED $50s AND $100s
AT 0600 TOMORROW.

15:59.393 --> 16:02.222
LOCATION WILL FOLLOW.
NO POLICE, OR H.D. IS DEAD."ANY PROOF OF LIFE?

16:02.222 --> 16:05.225
NO.HUH.

16:05.225 --> 16:08.184
DO NOT SAY ANYTHING BAD
TO MRS. DUBLIN.

16:08.184 --> 16:10.447
THAT IS AN ORDER.

16:10.447 --> 16:13.015
JAWOHL, MEIN KOMMANDANT.CAN I SEE?YEAH.

16:13.015 --> 16:14.756
WHERE IS MRS. DUBLIN?

16:14.756 --> 16:17.759
YEAH, SHE CRIES A LOT. THEN SHE
HAS TO FRESHEN HER MAKEUP,

16:17.759 --> 16:19.804
AND THEN SHE CRIES AGAIN.
SORT OF A CYCLE.

16:19.804 --> 16:22.242
THREE
DELIBERATE MISSPELLINGS

16:22.242 --> 16:24.244
AND AN OBVIOUS
MILITARY LILT,

16:24.244 --> 16:26.420
WHICH SUGGESTS THAT
THE WRITER IS NOT A VETERAN

16:26.420 --> 16:29.466
BUT WANTS US TO BELIEVE
THAT HE OR SHE IS--

16:29.466 --> 16:32.382
SO A NOTCH OR TWO LESS CLEVER
THAN HE OR SHE THINKS

16:32.382 --> 16:34.776
THAT THEY ARE,
USING THIS CRIME TO EXPRESS

16:34.776 --> 16:38.432
SOME KIND
OF DEEP, PERSONAL GRUDGE.

16:38.432 --> 16:41.348
THE VIOLENCE IS
AUTHENTIC ENOUGH.

16:41.348 --> 16:42.958
OH, MY LORD. WHAT NOW?
WHAT'S HAPPENED?

16:42.958 --> 16:45.047
IT'S--IT'S NOTHING,
GISELLE.

16:45.047 --> 16:48.007
THESE ARE MY COLLEAGUES.
PLEASE REMAIN CALM.HOW CAN I REMAIN CALM?

16:48.007 --> 16:51.227
I CAN'T RAISE
A MILLION DOLLARS BY TOMORROW!

16:51.227 --> 16:55.362
WE AREN'T NEARLY AS RICH
AS PEOPLE THINK.

16:55.362 --> 16:58.365
WH-WHAT DO I DO?I CAN'T SPEAK TO
THE FINANCIAL ASPECTS, MA'AM.

16:58.365 --> 17:00.715
THAT'S YOUR CALL.

17:00.715 --> 17:03.935
NOW CAN YOU THINK
OF ANYBODY WHO MAY HAVE HAD

17:03.935 --> 17:06.112
A PERSONAL GRUDGE
AGAINST YOUR HUSBAND?

17:06.112 --> 17:08.331
NO. NOBODY.

17:08.331 --> 17:10.725
MY HUSBAND IS A RESPECTED
AND BELOVED MEMBER

17:10.725 --> 17:12.596
OF SACRAMENTO SOCIETY.

17:12.596 --> 17:14.946
AND YOU?

17:14.946 --> 17:17.645
DO YOU RESPECT
AND BELOVEHIM?

17:17.645 --> 17:19.690
OF COURSE I DO.

17:19.690 --> 17:22.780
DEEPLY. WHAT A QUESTION.

17:22.780 --> 17:26.436
WELL, WH-WHY DON'T YOU WANT
TO RAISE A MILLION DOLLARS

17:26.436 --> 17:29.352
TO SAVE HIS LIFE?WHY DO YOU ASK THAT? I DO!

17:29.352 --> 17:31.354
WELL, THE WATCH
AND THE EARRINGS--

17:31.354 --> 17:33.530
THAT'S, LIKE, QUARTER MIL
RIGHT THERE.

17:33.530 --> 17:35.750
YOU CAN RAISE THE MONEY.
YOU'RE CONFLICTED,

17:35.750 --> 17:38.753
BECAUSE YOU DON'T KNOW
IF YOU WANT YOUR HUSBAND BACK.

17:38.753 --> 17:41.364
YOU DON'T LIKE YOUR HUSBAND
VERY MUCH AT ALL.

17:41.364 --> 17:43.323
YOU'RE ACTUALLY
A VERY GOOD ACTRESS

17:43.323 --> 17:46.239
PLAYING THE PART
OF THE LOVING WIFE.

17:46.239 --> 17:48.284
THAT'S WHAT I THINK
YOU ARE.

17:48.284 --> 17:51.026
CAN YOU LOOK AT ME
AND TELL ME THAT I'M WRONG?

17:51.026 --> 17:54.073
[sighs]

17:55.726 --> 17:56.988
DUH.

17:59.556 --> 18:03.169
OF COURSE I DON'T LIKE HIM
VERY MUCH.

18:03.169 --> 18:05.562
EVERYBODY IN THE KNOW
KNOWS THAT HARVEY DUBLIN IS

18:05.562 --> 18:09.392
A MEAN, LYING, BACKSTABBING,
CROOKED SON OF A BITCH.

18:09.392 --> 18:11.829
BUT I'M HIS WIFE,

18:11.829 --> 18:15.311
AND WHAT AM I SUPPOSED TO DO
BUT ACT LIKE I LOVE HIM?WHY DIDN'T YOU LEAVE HIM?

18:15.311 --> 18:17.879
[sighs] HAVE YOU EVER
DIVORCED A MEAN LAWYER?

18:17.879 --> 18:21.187
HE HAS NO RECORD
OF ANY PERSONAL WRONGDOING.

18:21.187 --> 18:23.232
HE'S A RESPECTED LOBBYIST.

18:23.232 --> 18:25.408
AN EXTORTIONIST AND CON MAN,
MORE LIKE IT.

18:25.408 --> 18:27.454
SO THERE ARE A LOT OF PEOPLE

18:27.454 --> 18:30.457
WHO MAY HAVE WANTED
TO HARM YOUR HUSBAND.ARE YOU KIDDING?

18:30.457 --> 18:33.329
THERE'S PEOPLE ALL OVER THE CITY
PRAYING THAT HE STAYS GONE.

18:33.329 --> 18:35.897
HOW ABOUT YOU?ME?

18:35.897 --> 18:37.986
YEAH, YOU.

18:37.986 --> 18:41.511
OH, I'LL RAISE THE MONEY.
I OWE HIM THAT MUCH.

18:41.511 --> 18:43.557
I KNEW WHAT I WAS MARRYING.

18:43.557 --> 18:45.559
YES, MR. DUBLIN IS
THE TARGET OF SOME LAWSUITS.

18:45.559 --> 18:47.778
MOST PROMINENT MEN ARE
AT ONE POINT OR ANOTHER

18:47.778 --> 18:51.347
IN THEIR CAREERS.
IT'S A HAZARD OF MODERN LIFE.

18:51.347 --> 18:54.133
SO HARVEY DUBLIN'S A SAINT.
THAT'S YOUR POSITION?

18:54.133 --> 18:56.352
NO, HARVEY DUBLIN IS NOT
A SAINT,

18:56.352 --> 18:58.267
BUT I'M HIS LAWYER,
AND I SPEAK FOR HIM.

18:58.267 --> 19:00.269
LOOK, HARVEY STARTED
WITH LESS THAN NOTHING.

19:00.269 --> 19:03.664
HE WAS A STREET KID.
HIS PARENTS WERE DRUG ADDICTS.

19:03.664 --> 19:07.102
HE LIVES IN FEAR OF FALLING
BACK INTO THAT WORLD,

19:07.102 --> 19:09.539
SO MAYBE HE PUSHES
A LITTLE BIT TOO HARD.

19:09.539 --> 19:12.020
MAYBE HE'S JUST
A LITTLE BIT TOO INTENSE

19:12.020 --> 19:15.458
IN HIS DESIRE TO WIN. THIS IS
AMERICA. THAT'S NO CRIME.SEVEN LAWSUITS PENDING.

19:15.458 --> 19:18.853
LOOK, ANYONE CAN GET SUED.
IT DOESN'T MEAN A THING.

19:18.853 --> 19:21.377
HALF THE PLAYERS IN THIS TOWN
ARE IN BED WITH DUBLIN

19:21.377 --> 19:24.293
ONE WAY OR ANOTHER.
IN FACT, YOUR, UH,

19:24.293 --> 19:25.860
YOUR NEW DIRECTOR,
GALE BERTRAM--

19:25.860 --> 19:28.079
HE'S ONE OF HIS CODEFENDANTS.REALLY?

19:28.079 --> 19:29.907
YEAH. BANK OF CLAREMONT vs.

19:29.907 --> 19:31.518
BRIXHAM LAKE DEVELOPMENT
CORPORATION AND OTHERS.

19:31.518 --> 19:34.477
IT'S GONNA BE A BLOCKBUSTER.DO GO ON.

19:34.477 --> 19:37.263
IT'S A COMPLEX
LAND/WATER RIGHTS THING.

19:37.263 --> 19:39.352
IT'LL RUN FOR YEARS.

19:39.352 --> 19:41.571
THE POINT IS,
BERTRAM WAS NAMED CODEFENDANT

19:41.571 --> 19:45.096
TO PUT PRESSURE ON THE DEFENSE
TO SETTLE EARLY.

19:45.096 --> 19:47.882
HAPPENS ALL THE TIME.HMM. THAT'S INTERESTING
ABOUT BERTRAM.

19:47.882 --> 19:50.058
NO, IT'S NOT.YES, IT IS.

19:50.058 --> 19:52.060
WHO'S TO GAIN THE MOST,
LEGALLY SPEAKING,

19:52.060 --> 19:54.062
IF MR. DUBLIN DOESN'T RETURN?

19:54.062 --> 19:56.282
WELL, THAT'S, UH,
THAT'S HARD TO SAY.

19:56.282 --> 19:58.284
TOO MANY VARIABLES
IN THE EQUATION.

19:58.284 --> 20:00.286
BUT HE IS COMING BACK,
RIGHT?

20:00.286 --> 20:02.636
I MEAN, IF GISELLE PAYS
THE KIDNAPPERS,

20:02.636 --> 20:04.681
WHY SHOULDN'T HE?WELL, STUFF HAPPENS.

20:04.681 --> 20:07.293
UH, DID YOU EVER SERVE
IN THE MILITARY, MR. COLMAN?

20:07.293 --> 20:11.210
NO, I DIDN'T HAVE
THAT HONOR. WHY DO YOU ASK?STANDARD QUESTION.

20:11.210 --> 20:12.602
[speaks inaudibly]

20:12.602 --> 20:14.169
WELL, HEY, DON'T JUST--

20:14.169 --> 20:15.649
[scoffs] OH, SHOOT.

20:15.649 --> 20:17.651
HEY, LADY, WAIT UP.

20:17.651 --> 20:19.522
MA'AM,
WE JUST WANT TO TALK.

20:19.522 --> 20:21.307
BLAH, BLAH, BLAH, BLAH.

20:21.307 --> 20:24.179
YEAH, BLAH, BLAH, BLAH. LISTEN,
DID YOU HEAR ABOUT THAT GUY

20:24.179 --> 20:27.487
THAT WAS KIDNAPPED UP THE STREET
A COUPLE BLOCKS OVER?

20:27.487 --> 20:30.403
HIS DRIVER WAS SHOT DEAD.OH, THAT. YEAH. ISN'T THAT WILD?
EVERYBODY'S TALKING ABOUT IT.

20:30.403 --> 20:34.363
WHAT EXACTLY ARE PEOPLE SAYING?ALL KINDS OF STUFF. FRIEND
OF MINE SAID SHE WAS THERE.

20:34.363 --> 20:37.279
OH, YEAH?WELL, SHE'S ACTING
ALL MYSTERIOUS,

20:37.279 --> 20:40.413
LIKE, "I CAN'T TELL YOU
WHAT HAPPENED,"

20:40.413 --> 20:44.112
LIKE SHE'S A SECRET AGENT
OR WHATNOT.WHAT'S YOUR FRIEND'S NAME?

20:44.112 --> 20:47.463
YOURS FOR $50.THIS IS
A MURDER INVESTIGATION.

20:47.463 --> 20:50.336
WE COULD TAKE YOU IN
RIGHT NOW FOR OBSTRUCTION.

20:50.336 --> 20:53.295
OH, BABY, SAVE YOURSELF
TIME AND PAPERWORK.

20:53.295 --> 20:56.385
I GOT 40... 43 BUCKS.

20:59.170 --> 21:01.042
UH... 12 CENTS.

21:01.042 --> 21:03.610
MONEY'S TIGHT ALL OVER, HUH?

21:03.610 --> 21:06.569
COME ON.
CUT US A BREAK HERE.

21:11.487 --> 21:14.403
SUGAR--BIG OLE TALL GIRL,
PINK HAIR.

21:14.403 --> 21:16.449
SHE'LL BE AROUND TOMORROW NIGHT.

21:16.449 --> 21:18.973
NICE DOIN' BUSINESS WITH YA.

21:18.973 --> 21:21.367
12 CENTS? SERIOUSLY?

21:21.367 --> 21:23.325
WHAT? [sighs]
SHE CLEANED ME OUT.

21:23.325 --> 21:25.153
[chuckles] 12 CENTS.

21:29.418 --> 21:31.464
AH.

21:31.464 --> 21:33.509
INTERESTING
ABOUT BERTRAM, HUH?

21:33.509 --> 21:36.512
YOU SAID THAT BEFORE.
NO, IT'S NOT.

21:36.512 --> 21:39.907
I GOT A WEIRD VIBE
THE FIRST MOMENT I MET HIM.

21:39.907 --> 21:42.475
UH, THE DIRECTOR OF
THE DIVISION OF LAW ENFORCEMENT

21:42.475 --> 21:44.781
DID NOT KIDNAP
HARVEY DUBLIN.

21:44.781 --> 21:46.827
SO YOU THINK.
HOW WELL DO YOU KNOW HIM?

21:46.827 --> 21:48.829
THIS IS YOUR REVENGE,
ISN'T IT?

21:48.829 --> 21:50.918
WELL, I-I AM SIMPLY
GONNA IGNORE YOU.

21:50.918 --> 21:53.442
I'M NOT PUNISHING YOU,
THOUGH YOU DO DESERVE IT.

21:53.442 --> 21:57.490
DUBLIN TURNED OUT TO BE
THE SLEAZEBAG I GUESSED HE WAS.

21:57.490 --> 22:00.144
HE DESERVES JUSTICE
LIKE EVERYBODY ELSE.

22:00.144 --> 22:02.451
OH, YOU'RE A COP.
YOU HAVE TO SAY THAT.

22:02.451 --> 22:04.453
YOU DON'T REALLY
BELIEVE IT.

22:04.453 --> 22:06.325
MY FINGERS ARE IN MY EARS.

22:32.786 --> 22:34.396
MORNING!

22:34.396 --> 22:37.094
HEY!

22:37.094 --> 22:38.835
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

22:38.835 --> 22:41.925
NOTHING YET.NO KIDDING.
WHERE'S THE MONEY?

22:41.925 --> 22:44.232
TRASH CAN DOWN THERE.THERE?

22:44.232 --> 22:45.886
YEAH.

22:45.886 --> 22:48.932
OH. JUST AS I THOUGHT.
NO ONE'S GONNA SHOW UP.

22:48.932 --> 22:52.371
LOOK AT THIS PLACE. IT'S FAR
TOO OPEN FOR A RANSOM DROP.WELL, THEY SAID NO POLICE,

22:52.371 --> 22:55.461
AND MAYBE THEY'RE STUPID ENOUGH
TO THINK THAT THERE'S NO POLICE.

22:55.461 --> 22:58.028
THEY KILLED A GUY
IN THE STREET.

22:58.028 --> 23:01.249
THEY HAVE TO KNOW
THE POLICE ARE INVOLVED. [sighs]

23:01.249 --> 23:03.599
THEY NEVER INTENDED
TO PICK UP THE RANSOM.

23:03.599 --> 23:05.906
WELL, MY HUNCH IS CORRECT.
THE KIDNAPPING'S A SHAM.

23:05.906 --> 23:08.604
DUBLIN'S ALREADY DEAD.WHAT WOULD BE THE REASON
FOR A PRETEND KIDNAPPING?

23:08.604 --> 23:10.606
WELL, THAT IS
THE SALIENT QUESTION, YES.

23:10.606 --> 23:14.175
BUT YOU CAN STOP WASTING
YOUR TIME HERE, CERTAINLY.

23:14.175 --> 23:17.961
HEY, DID MRS. DUBLIN
USE REAL MONEY OR FAKE MONEY?REAL.

23:17.961 --> 23:21.138
DID YOU LOOK AT IT?NO. WHAT WOULD
THAT MATTER NOW?

23:21.138 --> 23:22.749
WELL, IT DOESN'T MATTER.

23:22.749 --> 23:25.273
I'M--YOU KNOW,
I'M JUST A LITTLE CURIOUS.

23:25.273 --> 23:28.276
WHAT YOU'RE SAYING MIGHT BE
TRUE AND IT MIGHT NOT BE.

23:28.276 --> 23:31.322
WE STILL HAVE TO SIT ON
THIS THING FOR A LITTLE WHILE

23:31.322 --> 23:34.630
TO MAKE SURE NOBODY
SHOWS UP--COUPLE OF HOURS.WELL, THAT'S JUST SILLY.

23:34.630 --> 23:37.416
IT'S NOT SILLY.
IT'S PROFESSIONAL.PROFESSIONAL SH-MESSIONAL.

23:37.416 --> 23:39.418
JANE.

23:50.820 --> 23:53.301
[clatters]

23:53.301 --> 23:55.695
HEY, IT'S REAL!

23:55.695 --> 23:58.393
POLICE! FREEZE!
HANDS IN THE AIR!

23:58.393 --> 24:02.136
GET ON YOUR KNEES!
DO IT NOW! DO IT NOW!OKAY.

24:02.136 --> 24:04.268
DON'T MOVE.

24:10.884 --> 24:12.929
[man]
THE DIRECTOR IS EXPECTING

24:12.929 --> 24:15.932
A FULL BUT CONCISE
PROGRESS REPORT.HOW'S THAT JACKET SMELL?

24:15.932 --> 24:18.979
THIS IS A DIFFERENT SUIT.YEAH, BUT THE OTHER ONE'S
RUINED, ISN'T IT? HMM?

24:18.979 --> 24:20.371
POWER OF SUGGESTION.

24:20.371 --> 24:22.678
OKAY, YOU KNOW WHAT?
BITE ME.

24:28.467 --> 24:31.687
SO...
POOR HARVEY DUBLIN, HUH?

24:31.687 --> 24:34.516
SIR, NO ONE PICKED UP
THE RANSOM DROP,

24:34.516 --> 24:36.475
SO FOR THAT
AND OTHER REASONS,

24:36.475 --> 24:38.128
WE BELIEVE THAT

24:38.128 --> 24:40.130
THE KIDNAPPING ASPECT
OF THIS CASE IS A PRETENSE.

24:40.130 --> 24:43.090
MASKING WHAT?THAT WE CAN'T SAY FOR SURE.

24:43.090 --> 24:45.875
WE HAVE PROMISING LEADS.WELL, I NEED SOMETHING
TO TELL THE MEDIA.

24:45.875 --> 24:47.790
TELL 'EM
HARVEY DUBLIN'S DEAD.

24:47.790 --> 24:50.967
WELL, I'M SO GLAD YOU DECIDED
TO WORK ON THIS CASE, MR. JANE.

24:50.967 --> 24:52.926
YOUR DIRECTNESS IS BRACING.

24:52.926 --> 24:56.320
OF COURSE, PROCEDURALLY,
WE'RE STILL ASSUMING HE'S ALIVE,

24:56.320 --> 24:58.932
UNTIL WE HAVE
PROOF POSITIVE OTHERWISE.

24:58.932 --> 25:01.543
WHY KILL DUBLIN?
WH-WHAT'S THE MOTIVE?

25:01.543 --> 25:03.545
WELL, TWO POSSIBILITIES.

25:03.545 --> 25:05.504
UH, ONE--SIMPLE ROBBERY.

25:05.504 --> 25:07.854
THE CULPRIT WAS GOING
AFTER THE DIAMOND THAT, UH,

25:07.854 --> 25:10.509
DUBLIN ALWAYS CARRIES ON HIM.

25:10.509 --> 25:12.728
[chuckles]
DIAMOND? WHAT DIAMOND?

25:12.728 --> 25:14.730
WELL, APPARENTLY,
DUBLIN HAD A TERROR

25:14.730 --> 25:16.993
OF FALLING BACK
INTO POVERTY, OF, UH,

25:16.993 --> 25:19.605
DYING IN A PAUPER'S GRAVE
LIKE HIS FATHER DID,

25:19.605 --> 25:21.563
SO HE ALWAYS CARRIED
A LARGE DIAMOND WITH HIM,

25:21.563 --> 25:23.173
JUST IN CASE.

25:23.173 --> 25:25.828
IT'S KIND OF
A TOUCHING STORY, ISN'T IT?

25:25.828 --> 25:27.830
SO SOMEONE STAGED
THIS ABDUCTION

25:27.830 --> 25:30.703
TO STEAL THE DIAMOND.

25:30.703 --> 25:33.532
OKAY. UM, WHERE'S
